2008 Beijing Olympics will forever have a warm place in my memory. Its not like I was a huge fan of the event or anything, gosh I was only 11 at the time; I couldn't care less on what was being competed. I did, however, remember watching the olympics in my parents room with my family, snuggling tightly with my brother, mom, and dad under one blanket. I remember being awed by the grand fireworks that danced through Beijing's dark skyline. I remember David Beckham doing a freekick on an iconic red double decker london bus for the succeeding olympics. But most of all I remember the Birds Nest, this interesting organic-like metal construction that filled with life during the olympics.
.
This summer I had the opportunity to visit the Birds Nest firsthand. Its bigger than I remembered from the TV 9 years ago. For me, the Birds Nest is more then just a modern metal structure. It is, at the very least, a heartwarming memory. #beijing #birdsnest #china #architecture_view #architecture
